    "body": "This has been fixed in the latest unreleased version:\r\nThe location keyword (`memory` or `storage`) is enforced. If you use `memory` it works fine. If you use `storage` the compiler reports a `DeclarationError` about the uninitialized storage pointer. If you declare storage structs and point to them, it also works fine.",
